      "message": "I don\u0027t work in Skia much, so this is up to you :D - but this reads a bit confusing to me - with the previous call you could know what sampling mode would be used. With this mip-specific call, it\u0027s less clear what sampler state you\u0027ll get without reading the function. Just reading, I could see getting either linear or nearest if mipMapped \u003d false.\n\nGiven that the only use of refTextureProxy with the mipMapped arg is here, I wonder if it\u0027s clearer to add a \"GrSamplerState::ClampMipMap()\" helper, and call refTextureProxyForParams with either ClampNearest or ClampMipMap, depending on the mipMapped var? Otherwise, maybe an additional comment in the header would help?\n\nup to you though.",
